OL,6,F"I return to the particular tragedy of
OL,7,Fthis case and the fact you have lived
OL,8,Fwith the knowledge of what you did for
OL,9,F25 years. You have thought about this,
OL,10,Fquote, 'a million times' but couldn't
OL,11,Factually say the words.
OL,13,F"This can be seen as consistent with
OL,14,Fyour personality disorder traits. I'm
OL,15,Fclear this is not a case where you had
OL,16,Fa sense of having gotten away with it,
OL,17,Frather you lived isolated with this
OL,18,Fterrible and tragic knowledge for a
OL,19,Fquarter of a century."
