OL,6,FMrs Justice Eady sentences Sharkey to
OL,7,Ftwo years in jail, suspended for two
OL,8,Fyears
OL,10,FBut she later added: "I am satisfied
OL,11,Fthat this very sad case calls for
OL,12,Fcompassion, no useful purpose would be
OL,13,Fachieved by immediate imprisonment.
OL,15,F"I consider that appropriate
OL,16,Fpunishment can be achieved by a
OL,17,Fcustodial term that is suspended."
OL,19,FSharkey was seen shaking and in tears
OL,20,Fas she was handed the sentence.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/14
